<br>
Then she took her break and wrote OOP then said maybe she might write an 8th book if she feels like it.. <br>
<br>
So she is playing it cool saying that anything is possible but at the same time not committing to anything either.  While she has more money then she ever dreamed of, I am not sure she really wanted all the fame that went with it.  Part of why it took her 3 years to get book 5 out was she was very stressed out and worn out from all the hype and hoopla, thus she took a break in between book 4 and 5.  So I  wouldn't blame her for wanting to stop at book 7 if she wants too since that is all she committed to in the first place.<br>
<br>
With that said, depending on how she ends the series in book 7, I think will be the most telling on whether or not she will write any more HP books or even have a story line for another book or not.  <br>
<br>
Right now, I am just hoping she answers the majority of my questions/hints she has thrown out in the books, and wraps the series fairly well and nicely with the last book.<br>
<br>
I still can't wait for book 6 to see what happens in the war.<br>
<br>
